adviseScripts.text: Young Nikkes these days don't have any manners.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: When I give them advice as their senior, they either just yawn or scratch their heads.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Hey, Greenhorn. Do you think my advice is useless, too?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Don't you remember what it's like to be young?
Advice is the greatest gift that the old can give the young.
I used to think old folks didn't know anything, either.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Mmm... I see. I guess nothing's really changed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: That's exactly what I'm talking about!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: ... But, seeing how much they hate it, that may indicate that something's wrong with me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I have a discussion with Liter about giving advice.
Greenhorn, imagine you had a dog.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Now, imagine that dog was doing its business in a place where people don't usually go.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Would you clean it up, or just leave it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: It wouldn't be so bad to leave it, right? Just once?
I would still clean it up.
You rapscallion!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You don't deserve to be a dog owner!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: That's right! Of course you have to clean it up!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You can't just leave it even if nobody's around. You're going to make all of us dog owners look bad!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Hey, you're a pretty good dog owner, Greenhorn!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: ... I don't have the heart to tell Liter I don't actually have a dog.
Do you ever think about leashes?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: A lot of people think a leash restricts a dog's freedom.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But what do you think, Greenhorn?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: It's about their safety, not their freedom.
Dogs deserve their freedom.
That's a great response.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You never know when and where an accident will happen. We need to protect dogs.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Hmmm... I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Well, what good is freedom if you don't have safety?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You listen to me, youngster...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Liter about the benefits of the leash.
There are times you have to be strict with people when giving instructions for work.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I've been thinking if I've been too harsh recently... Well, I mean sometimes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Should I change my ways?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I think a change might do you good.
Being strict is a matter of safety.
Is that so.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But, I'm worried about everyone's safety.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: If I'm not strict, they'll get complacent quickly...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Hmmm... That's right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: If I'm strict, they are more careful. That's the most important.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I need to play the villain to make sure that everyone is safe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Liter lecture about lecturing.
Centi is such an amazing kid.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: She does everything I tell her, without any complaining.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But, I'm worried that she might become too dependent.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Centi is not a kid.
It's okay. She has you to watch out for her.
... Right. She probably has thoughts of her own, I suppose.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Soon, she will be independent enough to make it without me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Haha. When I think about it, delight and sorrow mix in my heart...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Haha! That's the right answer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: ... But, you know, even I will die one day.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I can't always be by her side.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Liter brag about Centi.
I'm getting older and older.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Someday, I will no longer do this work.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But every time I think about life without work, I get frustrated.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You should prepare for your retirement.
When that day comes, you'll find something else to do.
Retirement... I suppose you're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But, you know...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I don't know how meaningful life could be after being retired, if it can't be enjoyed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Do you truly think so?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Even when these old bones can't do this job anymore,
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: there's bound to be something else that I'll enjoy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Liter about the future.
About Ludmilla, there are moments when she seems too mature.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: As far as I know, she is much younger than me so I wonder why.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: ... Could she be lying about her age?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Maybe it's because of her high quality of life.
... Maybe it's because you're less mature than you thought?
Quality of life... I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I guess it doesn't matter how long you have lived. What's important is the quality of life you've lived...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... I understand. Thank you, Greenhorn.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Frankly, I'm offended.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I have a conversation with Liter about Ludmilla.
Why is Anis like that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Why does she keep taking her socks off everywhere?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I can only clean up after her for so long!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: From now on, if you see her socks lying around, just come and tell me.
It's a bit of a secret, but Anis actually has a medical condition with her feet...
... Greenhorn.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I'm actually speechless that you just said that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: ... Ah. Is that so.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Hmmm... I didn't even know, and I...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: ... You. You're lying.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Liter gossip about Anis for a while.
Mmmm... I got a new task at work,
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: but for some reason, I just can't seem to focus.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Maybe I'm getting old... Or maybe I'm just tired...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Maybe it's because you don't find the work interesting anymore?
You just need a good rest.
Oh. I think that might be it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I had an inkling that might be it. After all, the work is similar to what I've done before.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But I guess I'll just have to grin and bear it...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: If I slack off, who could replace me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: There are dozens of people who are relying on me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Thank you for your words, but I can't.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Liter talk about the work that she enjoys.
When I look at Volt, I always think to myself...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: What a great life to live.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: No one lives as comfortably as she does.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I'm envious.
Volt also has her own troubles.
... Don't be jealous of a dog.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: What? This bastard? No way.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Woof! Woof woof!
adviseScripts.speaker: Volt

adviseScripts.text: Argh! What's gotten into you all of a sudden?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I spend a good time with Volt.
I have a long-time customer. He's been coming to Mighty Tools for over 10 years.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: We're actually close enough that we've gone out to eat a couple of times.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: However, I recently discovered he's been tampering with the construction funds.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I'm at a loss. What do I do?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Give him a piece of your mind.
Let it slide so your relationship can remain intact.
That's what I was thinking.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But I keep psyching myself out and can't take the plunge. I was hoping someone could give me one last push.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: And thanks to you, I got just that!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You're right. He and I have a good thing going with our friendship.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: No matter what, I won't jeopardize that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Gosh, living in this world sure isn't easy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Liter tells me more about this customer that was giving her trouble.
I was thinking about picking up a new hobby.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: That board that Epinel rides looks like a lot of fun.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I was thinking about giving it a try.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But, aren't I a bit too old for that sort of thing?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: If you injure yourself at your age, you'll have a harder time recovering.
Age doesn't matter when it comes to hobbies.
*Bark*
adviseScripts.speaker: Volt

adviseScripts.text: Looks like Volt agrees with you. I guess you're right... It'd be bad news if I ended up hurting myself...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Oh, screw the both of you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You've got a point.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Come to think of it, Nikkes don't get any weaker when we age.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: All right, it's settled. I'll give it a shot.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I listened to Liter as she listed off all the reasons she wanted to give boarding a try.
I was thinking of getting Volt a younger brother.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I'm not at home a lot, and Volt looks like he's feeling a little lonely.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: If I get him a little brother to play with, he might not be as lonely.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Then you'll just end up with two lonely dogs instead of one.
How about bringing two more dogs?
You could be right...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: What I should do instead is just bring Volt with me wherever I go.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Two plus Volt... That'd be three dogs altogether.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: No, I can't take care of them like Biscuit.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Liter shares a few more of her worries about Volt with me.
Thanks to advances in medical technology and there not being any risk of car accidents or natural disasters,
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I've heard that the elderly population in the Ark is on the rise.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Apparently, there's been some friction between the younger populace and the elderly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: If you had to choose, who would you side with?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I don't want any part in it.
I can't choose. I see both sides.
You shouldn't ignore such important social issues!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You don't have to pick a side, but you should at least be following it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: It's important to listen to both sides of the story but...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: that could easily lead to indifference and you ignoring the issue, so be careful.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Liter and I debate about social issues.
Time catches up to all of us eventually. Even you'll grow old someday, Greenhorn.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: So, how old would you like to be?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I wanna become an old geezer.
I'd like to live as a hot charming middle-aged guy.
Haha, what a sight that would be!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Once you get old enough, you stop caring about what anyone else thinks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: It might be fun to be able to do whatever you want.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Well, you'll have to do more than just wish for it to make it happen.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You'd also need to have the looks for it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: However, for you Greenhorn, I can comfortably see that in your future.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Liter and I look up various ways on how to stay young.
There aren't any restaurants near the construction site I'm working at right now, so I've been packing my lunch.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: It wasn't so bad at first, but I'm starting to get a little tired of it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: What can I do to change things up?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I'll ask Emma if she can pack you a lunch.
I'll pack your lunch.
... Um, no thanks. That's all right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Haha. That's very sweet of you.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But I couldn't ask you to do that. I appreciate your offering though.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Liter and I discuss what we think is the perfect packed lunch.
Even I will die someday.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I know people say Nikkes are immortal, but nothing in this world lasts forever.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I already know what kind of death I want.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: What about you, Greenhorn? Is there any way you'd prefer to leave this world?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Surrounded by beautiful women.
Dying peacefully in my sleep.
Er... well, it's a free country, so if that's what you want...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: More power to you, I suppose.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I see...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: A lot of people prefer that kind of death.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But for you, it just seems so...ordinary.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Liter and I have a heavy conversation about death.
You can tell a lot about a person by how they clean. I get a big kick out of it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Rapi, to be honest, is kinda boring. She doesn't spill anything, and never makes a mess.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: If I see gunpowder residue everywhere, I know Neon is the culprit.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: And for Anis...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Soda cans lying everywhere?
Socks all strewn about?
Precisely. I think she has soda instead of blood pumping through her veins.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: She's always tossing the cans on the floor when she's done.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: At least put them all in one spot! Everywhere I go, I'm stepping on cans!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: If I see one more can, I'm gonna lose it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Yes! Why on earth does she take off her socks wherever she goes?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Just how many pairs of socks does she have, anyway?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You'd think she just wears them once and then buys another pair later.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Wait... I think that may be actually what's happening! That's it! I'm gonna go talk to her!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Liter and I look for Anis.
What are some of your favorite foods, Greenhorn?
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Me personally, I like...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Wait, no.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Try guessing what food I like.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: ... Porridge?
Dog treats?
C'mon, I'm not THAT old!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: But I do like eating porridge.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: *Bark*
adviseScripts.speaker: Volt

adviseScripts.text: Quit making fun of me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I don't like dog treats, okay?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: So stop looking at me like that!
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Liter and I talk about our favorite foods.
I'm loving this new toolset that I got.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Centi's eyes were practically green with envy.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: So I just...
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: You didn't poke her in the eye, did you?
Did you sell it for a premium?
I couldn't help myself... wait.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I would never do something like that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: I wouldn't say for a premium, but I did get a few Credits for it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Although I am Centi's master, the closer the relationship, the clearer the account.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: And after giving money, she will also treasure those tools more.
adviseScripts.speaker: Liter

adviseScripts.text: Liter teaches me how to distinguish good tools from bad.
